(511, 1, '2018-07-22 18:30:56', '2018-07-22 11:30:56', 'SOUTHEAST ASIA\'S WEIRD FICTION JOURNAL\r\n<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Skelos-Issue-1-Covers-680x500.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nIn its debut, SKELOS: THE JOURNAL OF WEIRD FICTION AND DARK FANTASY features a never-before-published fantasy piece by Robert E. Howard (Conan, Kull, Solomon Kane) illustrated by the legendary Mark Schultz (Xenozoic Tales, Coming of Conan, Prince Valiant). Also featured is a new sword and sorcery novelette by Keith Taylor (Bard series, Cormac Mac Art), a long-awaited sequel to his classic tale “Men from the Plain of Lir” originally published in WEIRD TALES.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Skelos-Issue-1-Covers-680x500.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Skelos-Journal-2-Covers-680x500.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n\r\nThe second issue of SKELOS: THE JOURNAL OF WEIRD FICTION AND DARK FANTASY features fantasy and horror fiction from some of the top names in the field, including World Fantasy Award winner Jessica Amanda Salmonson, British Fantasy Award winner Adrian Cole, Bram Stoker nominees Angeline Hawkes and Chad Hensley. Other authors include Cynthia Ward, Howard Andrew Jones, Scott Oden, Milton Davis, and W. H. Pugmire; novelettes by Robert M. Price and Jess Nevins.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Skelos-Journal-2-Covers-680x500.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<a href=\"#\" aria-label=\"previous\" aria-role=\"button\">\r\n\r\n</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\" aria-label=\"next\" aria-role=\"button\">\r\n\r\n</a>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/rocky-beach.jpg\" alt=\"rocky-beach\" />', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '156-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-22 18:30:56', '2018-07-22 11:30:56', '', 156, 'http://www.ombak.org/156-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(493, 1, '2018-07-22 17:59:49', '2018-07-22 10:59:49', '\n	SOUTHEAST ASIA\'S WEIRD FICTION JOURNAL\n			<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Skelos-Issue-1-Covers-680x500.jpg\" alt=\"\" />			\n				<p>In its debut, SKELOS: THE JOURNAL OF WEIRD FICTION AND DARK FANTASY features a never-before-published fantasy piece by Robert E. Howard (Conan, Kull, Solomon Kane) illustrated by the legendary Mark Schultz (Xenozoic Tales, Coming of Conan, Prince Valiant). Also featured is a new sword and sorcery novelette by Keith Taylor (Bard series, Cormac Mac Art), a long-awaited sequel to his classic tale “Men from the Plain of Lir” originally published in WEIRD TALES.</p>\n<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Skelos-Issue-1-Covers-680x500.jpg\" alt=\"\" />			\n			<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Skelos-Journal-2-Covers-680x500.png\" alt=\"\" />			\n				<p>The second issue of SKELOS: THE JOURNAL OF WEIRD FICTION AND DARK FANTASY features fantasy and horror fiction from some of the top names in the field, including World Fantasy Award winner Jessica Amanda Salmonson, British Fantasy Award winner Adrian Cole, Bram Stoker nominees Angeline Hawkes and Chad Hensley. Other authors include Cynthia Ward, Howard Andrew Jones, Scott Oden, Milton Davis, and W. H. Pugmire; novelettes by Robert M. Price and Jess Nevins.</p>\n<img src=\"http://www.ombak.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Skelos-Journal-2-Covers-680x500.png\" alt=\"\" />			\n				<a href=\"#\" aria-label=\"previous\" aria-role=\"button\"><svg version=\"1.1\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" viewBox=\"0 0 512 512\">\n<path d=\"M398.572,104.287L246.857,256.001l151.715,151.714c3.617,3.618,5.428,7.904,5.428,12.856c0,4.953-1.811,9.238-5.428,12.857 l-47.428,47.428c-3.619,3.619-7.904,5.428-12.857,5.428s-9.238-1.809-12.857-5.428l-212-212c-3.619-3.618-5.428-7.904-5.428-12.856 c0-4.953,1.81-9.238,5.428-12.857l212-212c3.619-3.618